        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer71070574" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5168535176984968300">Common McKillip themes exemplified by this trilogy:<br/><br/>1) There is nothing which cannot be faced, endured, known, understood. <br/>2) Art conquers all misfortunes. <br/>3) The mind is the most powerful weapon.<br/>4) He who plays God had better be prepared to be God, especially when God turns up and wants his housekeys back.<br/>5) Mess with teenage girls and the shit will be on.<br/>6) Stand by your man. Even if it means turning pirate to hunt the dead bastard down.<br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


